- Use `docker run -it --privileged --mount type=bind,source=.,target=/app mermin-builder:latest /bin/bash -c "cargo test [OPTIONS] [TESTNAME] [-- [ARGS]...]"` to run tests.
- Use `docker run -it --privileged --mount type=bind,source=.,target=/app mermin-builder:latest /bin/bash -c "cargo clippy [OPTIONS] [--] [<ARGS>...]"` to run clippy.
- Use `docker run -it --privileged --mount type=bind,source=.,target=/app mermin-builder:latest /bin/bash -c "cargo ..."` to run any cargo commands.
- Use `docker run -it --privileged --mount type=bind,source=.,target=/app mermin-builder:latest /bin/bash -c "cargo run [OPTIONS] [ARGS]..."` to run the binary.
- Use `docker run -it --privileged --mount type=bind,source=.,target=/app mermin-builder:latest /bin/bash -c "cargo build [OPTIONS]"` to run the agent.
- Use `docker run -it --privileged --mount type=bind,source=.,target=/app mermin-builder:latest /bin/bash -c "bpftool [OPTIONS] OBJECT { COMMAND | help }" to run bpftool commands.
- Use `docker run -it --privileged --mount type=bind,source=.,target=/app mermin-builder:latest /bin/bash -c "llvm-objdump [options] <input object files>" to run llvm-objdump commands.
- This is required because aya-ebpf will not compile properly on a non-linux host machine.
